1.title: Bristol Race to $200K
1.plot: The second annual Bristol No Prep race begins with 32 of the fastest men and women competing for a giant, winner takes all, prize of $200,000. The competition heats up as racers push their cars round after round adjusting their tunes for the track.

1.title: Midnight Riders
1.plot: Check out the new series Street Outlaws, Mondays at 10PM E/P. Oklahoma City's fastest street racers compete for spots on their top ten list. When race day comes, fights break out that leave shockwaves throughout this racing community.

2.title: Young and Old Blood
2.plot: Check out the new series Street Outlaws, Mondays at 10PM E/P. Local legend Varley is devastated when he's told he must quit street racing. Chuck begs Big Chief to coach him back up the list but while testing his car, Chuck is swarmed by cops.

3.title: Stand Your Ground
3.plot: Chuck (#7) and Flip's (#6) smack talk at a poker tournament leads to another call out. Monza (#4) calls out groom-to-be Daddy Dave (#3) for his spot but days before his wedding, Daddy Dave's test hits signal the boys in blue.

4.title: Murder the Nova
4.plot: While preparing to race Doc (#2), Murder Nova (#1) does a test hit on the street that draws the attention of the local authorities. Team Varley (#9) and Farmtruck (#10) scramble to get their cars ready to rematch.

5.title: King of the Streets
5.plot: Check out the new series Street Outlaws, Mondays at 10PM E/P. After three years of taunting, Doc (#2) calls out Murder Nova (#1) to race for the crown.

6.title: Racer's Revenge
6.plot: Doc (#1) and Shawn (#2) face each other in a rematch for the Crown of Oklahoma's fastest street car. Derek calls out Farmtruck (#10) and tries to get back on the list, but during a late night testing session, Derek gets a visit from some familiar cops.

7.title: Last Car Standing
7.plot: The rivalry between Daddy Dave (#2) and Shawn (#1) comes to a head when Dave calls out Shawn for the #1 spot. Fresh off his win against Farmtruck (unranked) and cocky as ever, newcomer Derek (#10) challenges Varley (#9).

8.title: Interstate Showdown
8.plot: The Red River Rivarly gets renewed in a battle between Texas vs. Oklahoma drivers. The winner lays claim to being the fastest state in the country. Meanwhile,Farmtruck and Asian take a roadtrip of their own into Texas to do some old fashioned Â'fishing'.

1.title: Lonestar Smackdown
1.plot: In the season premiere, Farmtruck and AZN must face-off against newbie racers who want to get on the top ten list. Old state rivalries lead to big brawls when Texas racers LMR want to change the rules on the OKC guys.

2.title: Midwest Fireworks
2.plot: Big Chief strikes a deal with loudmouth racer Freakin' Rican, allowing him to call out #10 Farmtruck in exchange for bootleg fireworks.There's a shakeup in the middle of the list when #8 Derek gets called out by newcomer #9 Andrade,

3.title: Sonoma Mr. Nice Guy
3.plot: After an expensive overhaul of his car, #2 Murder Nova calls out #1 Daddy Dave in an unforgettable rematch showdown. Freakin' Rican finally gets his shot when he calls out #10 Farmtruck, but an AZN joyride jeopardizes the Farmtruck's gatekeeper standing.

4.title: Fastest Chick in OKC
4.plot: Tina Pierce, known by locals to be the fastest female racer in Oklahoma, calls out #10 Farmtruck. Old family rivalries come to a head when #8 Varley and #9 Andrade Jr. face-off while #6 Chuck and #7 Derek race for a $1000 and the #6 spot.

5.title: Showdown Lowdown
5.plot: #1 Daddy Dave and #2 Murder Nova square off while best friends #3 Doc and #4 Monza battle on the street for the first time. After installing a secret weapon on his Monte Carlo, Doc is painfully reminded that testing on the street is very illegal.

6.title: Drag Week
6.plot: With the help of some racing legends, Big Chief resurrects his first race car, a '72 Pontiac LeMans he calls The Crow. The OKC's top 3 take on some expert race car builders' best to hold their coveted title of "Fastest Street Cars in the Nation."

7.title: Papa's Got a Brand New Bug
7.plot: AZN and Farmtruck build a Volkswagen bug race car to go out fishing with, but have a run-in with the local authorities. The top 3 on the list compete in a racing extravaganza. Big Chief re-introduces The Crow to the racers by calling out the #1 spot.

8.title: Straight Out to Cali
8.plot: Crazy Kelly, along with his California racing cronies, call out OKC's best and fastest. The OKC crew bring their cars out to Compton for a showdown of pride and high stakes betting while AZN and Farmtruck head to Chicago to fish for races.

1.title: The Rise of the Crow
1.plot: Big Chief relinquishes his racemaster duties to another driver so he can race THE CROW back up the list. Tina drops off the list, opening the coveted 10-spot for a round robin competition. Varley's son/driver is a no show. Azn gets stopped by the police.

2.title: Go Back to Tulsa
2.plot: Track racers from Tulsa call out the 405 with hopes of taking down the "fastest street-raced cars in the country". Farmtruck and AZN attempt a garage sale. Both Murder Nova and Chuck upgrade to twin turbo.

3.title: Top 5 List Shake-Up
3.plot: Racemaster Farmtruck devises a plan to have the top 5 racers battle each other to shake up the top 10 list. AZN fishes for races with the Dung Beetle as Varley's son Shelby takes over the Gold Car driving duties and attempts to get them back on the list.

4.title: The Mouthy Dirty South
4.plot: The OKC's best drivers roadtrip to The Big Easy to take on New Orleans' fastest street cars. Big Chief resurrects Flip's El Camino. Texan racer Boosted GT tries to get on the 405's list.

5.title: What's Up Doc
5.plot: Doc is determined to make a comeback with the Street Beast. Big Chief and Kamikaze decide it's time for the El Camino to race for the list. Farmtruck and AZN go after redemption with an old rival with the Dung Beetle.

6.title: Dallas Cash Days
6.plot: OKC racers take on the fastest of the south at the annual Cash Days race. While fishing for street races and fast cash, Farmtruck and AZN meet their match.

7.title: Big Chief vs. Murder Nova
7.plot: Big Chief finally calls out his best friend Murder Nova, in hopes of taking the #1 spot from Daddy Dave. Drag racer Kayla Morton and former Texan Boosted GT take their shot at the list. Farmtruck's dream for a new sleeper becomes AZN's worst nightmare.

8.title: It's Good to Be the Chief
8.plot: Big Chief sets his sights on beating Monza and Daddy Dave and finally claiming the #1 spot. Varley upgrades the Gold Car and tries to make it back on the top ten list.

1.title: Down from Chi-Town
1.plot: Oklahoma City's fastest take on the trash-talking street racers from Chicago. When many of the races get rained out, both sides agree to a rematch in Oklahoma. Meanwhile, the Farmtruck is back to its old 'fishing' ways, reeling in a Ferrari and a Camaro.

2.title: Shut Your Death Trap
2.plot: The Farmtruck is back, with a new bad ass motor and Chuck has his turbos lined out on The Death Trap. They both want back on the list. It's a war on the streets of the 405 with some of the fastest, closest drag racing ever.

3.title: Ova for Murder Nova?
3.plot: Chief and Shawn plan to take over the list, but no one's going to make it easy! Not #1 Monza, #2 Daddy Dave, or Doc coming up from the #5 spot. Dead batteries and loud mouth Texans mess with Shawn's head, enough where he considers dropping off the list.

4.title: Small Tire Shootout
4.plot: Chuck puts on a Small Tire Shootout in OKC, where the fastest small tire cars from the surrounding area will race each other for a $2,000 prize. Meanwhile, Farmtruck and Asian head to a Car Show in Kansas, where they race various show cars.

5.title: Gatekeeper Gate
5.plot: The fastest gatekeeper in Top Ten List history must defend against the loudest, angriest racers who want a shot at the list. Tensions are running so high, that Big Chief has to call a second race night in one week just to keep racers from coming to blows.

6.title: Vocal Local Yokels
6.plot: The 405 goes head-to-head in a demolition derby while Farmtruck and AZN answer a nasty callout. Then the legitimacy of the 405's entire list gets called into question, and it comes down to a 405 grudge match.

7.title: Hearse and the Wichita Curse
7.plot: Big Chief gets a call out from the 316 area code, Wichita, Kansas. Some of the 405's fastest racers must take on guys with names like the Murder 56 and Superman. Farmtruck and AZN get some seat time in the haunted hearse

8.title: Let Them Eat Crow!
8.plot: As the racing season winds down, everyone makes a final push to move up the top ten list. Big Chief gets a shot, but Daddy Dave pulls out all the stops to keep the crown. Farmtruck and AZN fish out new competition, but get more than they bargained for.

9.title: The Southeast's Fastest: Part 1
9.plot: On the final night of Cash Days, the remaining 405 racers put their reputation on the line as one of them tries to win $16,000 and be crowned the fastest street racer in the Southeast. Meanwhile, Farmtruck and AZN set their sights on a new World Record.

10.title: The Southeast Fastest, Part 2
10.plot: Conclusion to the two day race event.

11.title: Bumper to Bumper: The Secrets of Street Outlaws
11.plot: A behind the scenes look into the 405 racers' lives, with never-before-seen footage, sneak peeks and best-of moments. Their day jobs and financial sacrifices are revealed as well as their families feelings about racing.

1.title: New Orleans Cookin'
1.plot: Chief wants to do a "nationwide call out", but also wants to determine if Kye Kelly should be one of the Nation's top 5 drivers. So he sets up a showdown in New Orleans between the 405 and Kye and his Mississippi friends. Dave also wants a rematch for #1.

2.title: Permanent Gatekeeper
2.plot: Kamikaze takes the El Camino off the list, so Chief decides to round up 4 drivers and have a round robin race for the open 10-spot. Meanwhile, Farmtruck becomes the permanent gatekeeper of The List, and the guys at Midwest give Boosted an ultimatum: win.

3.title: She's a Good Girl
3.plot: Big Chief sets his sights on beating Monza and Daddy Dave and finally claiming the #1 spot. Varley upgrades the Gold Car and tries to make it back on the top ten list.

4.title: Small Tires, Big Dreams
4.plot: Boosted wants to be the first small tire car to crack the Top 5 on the List and make 405 History. Farmtruck is depressed from the death of Louise, so AZN brings someone new into the Farmtruck-AZN family. Dave opens up a new shop and has a new racecar.

5.title: Texas Grudge
5.plot: Boosted organizes some Grudge Races down in Fort Worth, Texas and also holds a Grudge Race school.

6.title: To Be #1 or Not to Be #1
6.plot: The 405 guys head to Los Angeles to take on some smack talking Street Racers. Farmtruck and AZN head for Hollywood, but run into some car problems. On Race Night, the tension between the 405 guys and the California racers escalate.

9.title: Round Robin Ridiculousness
9.plot: When Daddy Dave drops off the list, everyone moves up, leaving an open #10 spot. Big Chief decides to hold the largest round robin in 405 history to determine who is worthy and the winer must race the ultimate gatekeeper, Farmtruck.

10.title: 405 vs. Middle of 'Murica
10.plot: The 405 gets called out by 7 of the fastest racers from Colorado, Wyoming, Missouri and Kansas for a showdown on the street. Kamikaze needs to make money and brings back El Camino. Farmtruck and AZN prank Big Chief and Shawn by buying a "More-Door" Nova.

1.title: Kansas City Barbecue
1.plot: The 405 travel to Kansas City to accept a challenge of some smack talking racers. Farmtruck and AZN take on an elderly couple in a Hotrod. The 405 plan to prove their claim of being the "nation's fastest" by hosting the biggest Cash Days event in history.

2.title: No Rhino, No Cry
2.plot: The 405 List gets big shake-ups as everybody wants to move up, especially Dominator, who has been winning a lot recently. AZN is fed up with new puppy Suzi's biting antics so Farmtruck gets a dog trainer. Kamikaze takes a crack at the #10 spot.

3.title: Import This!
3.plot: The 405 gets an unusual callout from a bunch of mouthy racers with super fast import cars. Murder Nova, Chief, Chuck, Shane, Kamikaze and Boosted are in for a shock, when the ricer cars prove to be faster than anyone imagined.

5.title: David & Goliath vs. the 405
5.plot: Daddy Dave is finally ready to unveil his new racecar, "Goliath," and controversy brews as he wants to bully his way up the list. Farmtruck and AZN are convinced the firehouse is haunted and they call a medium to rid their abode of evil spirits.

6.title: Fear the Reaper
6.plot: After daves wrecks Goliath. Big chief finds a new racer to take up the number ten spot. He decides to put in a round robin to include the Reaper.

8.title: $50K, All the Way!
8.plot: Dissatisfied with the Nationwide Callout results Big Chief hosts an epic Cash Days 32 cars competing for $50K. Daddy Dave & The Sonoma, Kye Kelly with the NOLA crew & the OKC's fastest racers bring the heat. Who will be crowned "the fastest in the nation?

1.title: The Empire Builds Back
1.plot: Street Outlaws returns and OKC's biggest rivals attack the list with a vengeance. Jackie Knox wants on the list. Chief and Doc square off. Farmtruck and AZN go fishing, trying to give hell to a Hellcat.

2.title: It's Shane in the Membrane
2.plot: Chief goes head-to-head with Murder Nova. Farmtruck & AZN enter a small town, lawn mower drag race. Chief introduces new rules. Reaper and Shane get heated as they try to move out of striking distance of Jackie Knox in his world famous Sonoma.

3.title: Jumping the Shark-Pool
3.plot: Chief introduces an idea to make the list even faster...The Shark Pool. Now, a hungry group of street racers will be showing up every week to take on #10. Doc and Monza battle! Farmtruck schools a shark pool racer regarding an old debt.

4.title: Sharks After Dark
4.plot: With the popularity of the Shark Pool, Chief must host 2 race nights! Henson, Your Mom, and Chuck 55 all show up to challenge the gatekeeper, leaving Shane swimming for his survival. On the second race night, Chief and Shawn rematch for the top spot.

5.title: Daddy Day Car
5.plot: Daddy Dave returns as part of the Shark Pool with Henson's corvette 'Plan B,' along with new mother Tina Pierce and Boosted GT, after being dropped from the list. Farmtruck & AZN get a 'ricer' and the rivalry between Jackie and Shane burns hot.

6.title: Knockin' on Heaven's Door
6.plot: The 405 go head to head against Detroit's fastest. Big bets, big mouths and big crashes. Meanwhile the guys play around with a homemade bowling ball canon.

7.title: The Aftermath
7.plot: While Doc and Monza strategize for the number one and two spots, Big Chief deals with the aftermath of his crash. Meanwhile, Farmtruck takes on a new challenge.

8.title: Rebirth of the Crow
8.plot: Chief decides to get a new car while the battle for top list spots gets cutthroat. Doc takes another shot against #1 Shawn, Monza faces Reaper, Dave needs to get past Shane and new shark, Jeremy, must face the Farmtruck to get on the list.

9.title: The Crow also Rises...
9.plot: Chief unveils his new ride, The Crow-mod. Shawn challenges Doc, while Reaper races Monza. Farmtruck and AZN race the Dung Beetle against a car called "Bug killer." Fights break out between Dave's team and Reaper on race night.

10.title: Back on Track
10.plot: With the Crow-mod almost ready, Chief confronts his PTSD to get back behind the wheel.Ã'Â #3 Shawn faces #2 Monza in his new Camaro, Boosted returns, Reaper takes another shot at Dave, but tensions between him and Dave's crew make race night a debacle.

11.title: Ready, Set, Crow
11.plot: The Crow-mod finally makes a run for the list, facing the world famous Farmtruck for #10.Ã'Â Reaper and Shane battle for #5, while new lister Jeremy must face Dominator for his #6 spot.Ã'Â #4 Dave races #3 Monza while Shawn takes another shot at the #1 spot.

12.title: If You Can't Beat-le'em, Join 'em...
12.plot: Since everyone in the 405 has been upgrading their cars, it's time to go under their hoods to find out what makes these guys so fast.

1.title: Where the Streets Have No Name
1.plot: Since everyone in the 405 has been upgrading their cars, it's time to go under their hoods to find out what makes these guys so fast. Farmtruck and AZN struggle to fix the Dung Beetle for fishing, and setup some races to get out of paying for some tuning.

2.title: It's a Promod Party
2.plot: With faster cars than ever before trapped at the bottom, strategy and game playing take over list racing in the 405. Farmtruck and AZN salvage some explosive air bags. And on race night, it takes smart moves and a fast car to move up the new list.

3.title: OH-HI-NO
3.plot: When the 405 gets a last minute call-out from Ohio, it's a rush to get ready. Farmtruck and AZN fish out a Hot Rod and Kamikaze gets ready to bring the El Camino back. When Ohio arrives, the 405 tries to prove again they are the fastest on the street.

4.title: I Still Haven't Found What I'm Looking For
4.plot: The 405 list gets shaken up. Shane finds himself in a grudge race that ends in disaster, and on race night, Dave and Reaper can't agree on a call out.

5.title: I Will Follow
5.plot: The top racers feel the pressure with Dave in the top five and Chief in sixth place. Later, Chief and Boosted hold an emergency turbo school for Dominator; and Farmtruck and AZN find a flashy, orange fish.

6.title: 75,000 Reasons to Race
6.plot: The OKC crew travel south to race at the Texas Motorplex in the American Outlaws Live event.

7.title: Stuck in a Moment
7.plot: The 405 racers try to hang on to their spots on the list; and Farmtruck and AZN test the improved Farmtruck during a fishing race. Later, tension builds when Dave makes a call out for a race that he doesn't intend on participating in.

8.title: One
8.plot: The last list race of the season puts pressure on everyone; and Kamikaze and Farmtruck return to list racing.

9.title: Pride
9.plot: The crew from OKC competes against the best street racers in the U.S. at the American Outlaws Live event in hopes of winning the $75,000 grand prize.

10.title: Desire
10.plot:
Know what this is about?

11.title: Street Mission
11.plot: The 405 racers head to Memphis to compete against JJ "Da Boss." Chuck's prepared to prove himself.

12.title: Put Up for Your City
12.plot: Chief invites teams from Detroit, New York and California to race against the OKC; to see who is the baddest crew out there.

1.title: Street Outlaws vs. Fast N' Loud: Build to Mega Race Part III
1.plot: The Street Outlaws agree to race the guys from Fast n Loud, Farmtruck and AZN start on their budget build to race Aaron, while Chief and Shawn set out in search of the perfect car. When Chief hears rumors from Texas, he's not sure he wants to build a car.

2.title: Street Outlaws vs. Fast N' Loud: Build to Mega Race Part IV
2.plot: With only a week left, the team at Midwest Streetcars and Farmtruck and AZN are scrambling to get their cars ready to race. With little experience building cars on a schedule, both teams start to feel they might not be able to finish their cars in time.

3.title: Mega Race Build Up
3.plot: With Chief and his guys, Richard Rawlings and the Gas Monkeys, Farmtruck and AZN, and Aaron Kaufman all on the way to California for MegaRace, it's time to take a look back at the struggles they had while building their cars.

4.title: Street Outlaws vs. Fast N' Loud: The Mega Race
4.plot: With everyone finally in California, Chief and Richard get into it about who will drive their cars, and Farmtruck and AZN have to wait on Aaron. Then, it's time for the drivers to strap in, pull to the line, and race to see who has what it takes to win.

5.title: From Mega to Street
5.plot: The new season of Street Outlaws is about to begin and the 405 is moving away from Pro-mods on the street, so Chief and Shawn take a look back at how far the 405 has come. We show some deleted scenes from the big Mega Race.

6.title: Start Me Up
6.plot: Street Outlaws is back, and the guys in the 405 are making big changes. Chief decides to kick all the Pro-mods off the list. Then, it's time for an old school shakeup, everyone loses their spots and has to race to find out where they belong on the list.

7.title: I Can't Get No Satisfaction
7.plot: This week's race is all about the very top of the list and the very bottom. Ryan and Chuck are getting ready to battle for #1 again. At the bottom of the list, Farmtruck is feeling the heat and he does everything he can to hold onto a spot on the list.

8.title: Get Off My Cloud
8.plot: This week's race is all about the very top of the list and the very bottom. Ryan and Chuck are getting ready to battle for #1 again. At the bottom of the list, Farmtruck is feeling the heat and he does everything he can to hold onto a spot on the list.

9.title: Brand New Car
9.plot: With Chief set to take his new car up the list one more time, Reaper struggles to get his car fixed in time for race night. Farmtruck and AZN try and round up some races.

10.title: Sympathy for the Devil
10.plot: When JJ and his racers from Memphis come to OKC for two nights of racing, everyone in the 405 has to step up and get ready to lay it all on the line. But, after flagging and technicalities cause drama, the 405 has to fight for every win.

11.title: Can't You Hear Me Knocking
11.plot: Now that Chief is back on the list, he and Shawn map out a plan to get themselves back into the top spots. Farmtruck sets AZN up with a race against a doctor with a super car. And at race night, Doc seems like he finally has his car figured out.

12.title: Blinding Lights
12.plot: Detroit, New York and California each bring a team to compete against OKC; and five of the 405's racers step up.

13.title: Time is on My Side
13.plot: With only a few list races left, Chief takes out the Crow for testing. Plus, AZN has a new tune for the Dung Beetle and tests out the improvements.

14.title: Street Fightin' Man
14.plot: It's the last list race of the season, and everyone in the 405 is looking to make one more move towards the top. Then, on race night, some of the top guys don't bring their cars, and plans to move up the list blow up in Doc's and Chief's faces.

15.title: Midnight Rambler
15.plot: JJ "Da Boss" from Memphis comes to OKC to host a race, everyone who's anyone in street racing shows up to compete. With JJ going back to old school rules and a total of $60,000 on the line, the racers do anything and everything to win

16.title: Road to Number One
16.plot: In this episode, Chuck takes us back through every season of the show to look at the races and the strategies that got racers to the number one spot on OKC's top ten list. Chuck talks about what it takes to make it to the top and wear the 405 crown.

1.title: Smoked in Memphis
1.plot: The 405 heads Memphis, bringing everyone with them. However, that means racing on JJ's slick, asphalt road. When the 405's plan to stick together falls apart, they struggle to set up the right races and it looks like Memphis might get the best of them.

2.title: Memphis Blues
2.plot: As the epic battle between OKC and Memphis continues, Farmtruck and AZN take a look back at what happened between Memphis and the 405 to get them here. With a rematch between Chief and JJ coming up it promises to be another night for the history books.

3.title: Shut Up and Drive
3.plot: Chuck and Ryan look back at some of the biggest rivalries on the 405 list. Meanwhile, Farmtruck and AZN go head to head in a junky, clunker race.

4.title: Going for the Jugular
4.plot: It's the first list race of the season and that means everyone is gearing up for a fight. Then, with Chief's car down for repairs, Shawn tries to jump on the number one spot. But when Doc tries to hold off on racing Reaper, chaos breaks out on race night.

5.title: Blinding Lights Part 2
5.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

6.title: Down is the New Up?
6.plot: Chief commits to fall down the list on purpose in order to race everyone he missed on his last trip to the top. Meanwhile, Ryan and Chuck struggle to get their cars ready. Then, Shawn goes after Chuck in an attempt to take the OG Murder Nova back to #1.

7.title: Bad Beets
7.plot: With Chief out of town, Chuck takes over as racemaster, but still has to defend number one. Farmtruck & AZN dig up a new kind of race. Then on race night, with racers missing, Monza & Dave jump into the top five while Ryan tries to take Chuck's Crown.

8.title: He's the Chief
8.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

9.title: Bristol: Road to $100K
9.plot: It's the countdown to the biggest No Prep in Street Outlaws history & everyone is on their way to the legendary Bristol Motor Speedway. As they arrive, Farmtruck & AZN tell us about the race & give us a preview of all the racers competing for $100,000.

10.title: Bristol: Race to $100K
10.plot: The 405 are in Bristol, Tennessee to compete in the biggest no prep event in Street Outlaws history. With 32 of the baddest cars around competing for $100,000, the OKC racers give it everything they've got in order to take the win. It's Bristol, Baby!

11.title: It's Bristol, Baby!
11.plot: Ryan & Chuck show more behind the scenes footage of what the 405 got into while they were at Bristol. That includes Farmtruck & AZN finding some races & the guys from OKC getting ready to race. Plus we get a quick recap of where everyone is on the list.

12.title: Rules Change
12.plot: It's time for another list race in the 405 & new number one, Ryan Martin is getting ready to defend his crown. But on race night, Big Chief is back & he's brought new rules that are going to make race night move faster & keep the OKC racers on their toes.

13.title: What's Up, Doc?
13.plot: Shawn makes a tough decision regarding his spot on the list while Dominator fights to make it back on. Chief tweaks the rules once again. Ryan and Chuck face off at the top of the list and Chief's plan to fall down and race Doc finally comes true.

14.title: Outlaw Armageddon
14.plot: It's time for Outlaw Armageddon, the biggest & baddest No Prep race in the country, & the 405 gets ready for the race. Then, everyone who is anyone in the street & track races scenes comes to OKC to lay it all on the line and try to win the $40,000 prize.

15.title: Bottoms Up
15.plot: The 405 - the city's top 10 list of street racers - aim to reclaim their title as the fastest and most revered group of racers in the country.

16.title: Armageddon to the End
16.plot: After the first round of Outlaw Armageddon, there are still 19 of the best racers in the country left to fight it out for the $40,000 pot. The remaining 405 racers must fight to defend their turf, because being beat at their home track isn't an option.

17.title: Daily Battles
17.plot: The 405 battle it out in OKC. Chief races AZN. Doc and Chuck meet up for the first time ever.

18.title: 99 Problems
18.plot: With only two list races left in the season, the drivers work to get their cars race ready. Farmtruck and AZN prep for racing with some fishing. On race night Ryan is finally able to defend his spot and tempers flare between Doc and Monza.

19.title: Who Made These Rules?
19.plot: It's the final list race of the season, and everyone is aiming to move up. Murder Nova races Farmtruck for the first time and Ryan fights to reclaim the #1 spot. Chaos breaks out when Doc refuses a callout.

20.title: Countdown to Mega Motor Week
20.plot: It's the countdown to Discovery's first ever Motor Mega Week and that means a sneak peek at all the action. It's full of motor madness, including 3 all-new series premieres, plus the season finale of Street Outlaws: Memphis and all-new American Chopper.

21.title: Street Outlaws vs. Fast N' Loud: Start Your Engines
21.plot: Mega Race 2 starts with race master and NASCAR superstar, Kyle Busch.

22.title: Street Outlaws vs. Fast N' Loud: Build to Mega Race Gear 1
22.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

23.title: Street Outlaws vs. Fast N' Loud: Build to Mega Race Gear 2
23.plot: After losing to the 405 during the last Mega Race, Richard Rawlings wants a rematch and this time, he's going after current #1, Ryan Martin. The guys at Misfit Garage also callout Farmtruck and AZN for a race of their own, where they each build a new car.

24.title: Street Outlaws vs. Fast N' Loud: Build to Mega Race Gear 3
24.plot: The Misfits start their build but tempers flare when an argument breaks out, threatening to stall the build completely. Farmtruck and AZN work on transforming the Gonorail into a functioning vehicle, but learn that this build will take extra work.

25.title: Street Outlaws vs. Fast N' Loud: Build to Mega Race Gear 4
25.plot: Farmtruck and AZN and the Misfits complete their builds and make some test hits, but teams struggle with technical issues that must be corrected. Ryan arrives in Phoenix along with some fellow 405 racers while the Gas Monkey crew heads to Arizona to race.

26.title: The Fireball
26.plot: After getting called out by Richard Rawlings from Gas Monkey Garage, number one racer Ryan Martin has to work like crazy to get his car ready for the race. He and his team head out west to test, but it seems like everything is about to go wrong.

27.title: The Gonorail
27.plot: After accepting a challenge from the Misfits at Fired Up Garage, Farmtruck and AZN build themselves a road race vehicle. However, Farmtruck's vision to put a monorail car from the Oklahoma State Fair on wheels proves to be their biggest challenge ever.

28.title: Street Outlaws vs. Fast N' Loud: Driver's Meeting
28.plot: Farmtruck and AZN build The Gonorail for Mega Race 2.

29.title: Street Outlaws vs. Fast N' Loud: The Mega Race 2
29.plot: It's finally time for Mega Race 2, and that means that the racers from Street Outlaws, Fast N Loud, and Misfit Garage are all in Arizona for the big race. It's Oklahoma vs. Texas, and these guys will do anything to win.

1.title: The Story of Street Outlaws
1.plot: The Street Outlaws go in depth into how the show began and talk about what happened when producers came to Oklahoma for the very first time.

2.title: Playing Dirty
2.plot: When Reaper gets a smack talking call from a local dirt track owner, it turns into a dirt race challenge for the whole 405. After some testing, everyone from OKC comes to the track to try and prove they can be king of the street and king of the dirt.

3.title: Make My "Cash" Days
3.plot: Thirty-two of the fastest racers from around the country gather in OKC for the biggest street race of the year Cash Days. And, with $50,000 on the line, all the racers are prepared to push their cars to the limit to try and win it all.

4.title: Tech and Tune
4.plot: It's time for a new season of list racing in OKC and that means all the racers are upgrading and prepping their cars to be competitive. After lots of work, it's finally time to test the cars and see who's ready to dominate the list this season.

5.title: The Doc Amendment
5.plot: After a difficult end to last season's list racing, the 405 comes together to reassess the rules and make a plan to move forward. They all agree to a list shakeup, which means everyone loses his spot on the list and has to race to earn a new place.

6.title: No More Stalling
6.plot: After an unfinished list shakeup Ryan and Chief finally line up to race off for #1. With the list complete, the 405 gets ready for their first list race of the season.

7.title: Deja Vu
7.plot: It's a mad dash to make repairs as the top racers scramble to get ready to race. Meanwhile, Farmtruck and AZN head out of town to compete in a giant Daily Driver event.
